@Customers.Api_HostAddress = http://localhost:5003

### Service status
GET {{Customers.Api_HostAddress}}/
Accept: application/json

### Health
GET {{Customers.Api_HostAddress}}/health

### Get customer by ID (replace with actual ID from create response)
@customerId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
GET {{Customers.Api_HostAddress}}/api/customers/{{customerId}}
Accept: application/json

### Create customer (REST -> MassTransit command)
POST {{Customers.Api_HostAddress}}/api/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "companyName": "Acme Corp",
  "displayName": "Acme",
  "email": "billing@acme.example.com",
  "phone": "+39 02 1234567",
  "taxId": "IT12345678901",
  "vatNumber": "IT12345678901",
  "billingAddress": {
    "recipientName": "Acme Corp",
    "addressLine1": "Via Roma 1",
    "addressLine2": null,
    "city": "Milano",
    "stateOrProvince": "MI",
    "postalCode": "20100",
    "countryCode": "IT",
    "phoneNumber": "+39 02 1234567",
    "notes": null
  },
  "shippingAddress": null,
  "preferredLanguage": "it",
  "preferredCurrency": "EUR",
  "notes": "First customer"
}

### Update customer (partial – only set fields to change; replace id)
PUT {{Customers.Api_HostAddress}}/api/customers/{{customerId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "displayName": "Acme Italy",
  "phone": "+39 02 9876543",
  "notes": "Updated contact"
}

### Cancel customer (soft delete; replace id)
POST {{Customers.Api_HostAddress}}/api/customers/{{customerId}}/cancel
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cancellationReason": "Customer requested account closure"
}
